{"questionId":"22428664","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is acute, calculate&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>selecting sine rule formula&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> cosine rule formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4343</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mn>22</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mn>25</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4343</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>15</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4343</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em> for correct cosine rule formula to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8658</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9461</mn><mo>…</mo></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math> in the sine rule formula and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7267</mn><mo>…</mo></math> in the cosine rule formula.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22428664","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that AB^C is acute, calculate AB^C","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}